<i>Posted by Taludor on 07-30-2001 05:33 PM:</i>

<p><b> </b></p>

<p>I dont think <i>'Risk -vs- Reward'</i> is really applicable when your talking about places like Plane of Growth, and Fear perhaps.<br />
<br />
What exactly is the risk involved, at least at the level of play we and many others are at? A 20 minute CR? A zone does not pose a significant risk when the repop time is 12 hours. ToV presents a measure of risk not seen in PoG. If you screw up a pull you are looking at a possible reclearing of the area every 80 minutes or so untill you get it right. A raid can go nowhere fast when you cant drag the pull teams corpses out, and have to summon them back at the zone-in.<br />
<br />
Perhaps in Verrant's eyes, the reward is equal to the risk involved for Tunare. On the other hand, <i>Effort -vs- Reward</i> should be a focus for itemizing this NPC and other comparable NPC's. 12 hours for one drop is not going to happen again.<font face="verdana, arial, helvetica" size="2" ><br>
